  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is the best site to download songs?",
  "response": "When looking to download songs, it's important to use legal and reputable platforms to ensure that artists are fairly compensated for their work. Here are some of the best legal sites and services where you can download music:\n\n1. **[iTunes Store](https://www.apple.com/itunes/)**:\n   - Offers a vast library of songs and albums for purchase.\n   - Compatible with Apple devices and iTunes software.\n\n2. **[Amazon Music](https://music.amazon.com/)**:\n   - Provides a wide selection of songs available for purchase and download.\n   - Often offers competitive pricing and bundled deals.\n\n3. **[Bandcamp](https://bandcamp.com/)**:\n   - A favorite among independent artists and labels.\n   - Allows artists to set their own prices and often offers high-quality audio formats.\n\n4. **[Google Play Music](https://play.google.com/music) / [YouTube Music](https://music.youtube.com/)**:\n   - While Google Play Music has transitioned to YouTube Music, you can still purchase songs through YouTube Music.\n   - Offers a large catalog and integration with other Google services.\n\n5. **[Beatport](https://www.beatport.com/)**:\n   - Specializes in electronic music genres.\n   - Popular among DJs and electronic music enthusiasts.\n\n6. **[7digital](https://www.7digital.com/)**:\n   - Offers high-quality downloads across various genres.\n   - Provides both individual tracks and full albums.\n\n7. **[Free Music Archive (FMA)](https://freemusicarchive.org/)**:\n   - Hosts a vast collection of free, legal music downloads.\n   - Focuses on independent and Creative Commons-licensed music.\n\n8. **[SoundCloud](https://soundcloud.com/)**:\n   - While primarily a streaming platform, many artists offer tracks for free download.\n   - Great for discovering emerging artists and genres.\n\n9. **[Jamendo](https://www.jamendo.com/)**:\n   - Focuses on indie music with many tracks available for free download under Creative Commons licenses.\n   - Suitable for personal use and projects.\n\n**Subscription Services with Download Options:**\n\nSome streaming services also offer options to download songs for offline listening, though these typically require an active subscription and do not allow permanent ownership of the files:\n\n- **[Spotify](https://www.spotify.com/)**\n- **[Apple Music](https://www.apple.com/apple-music/)**\n- **[Tidal](https://tidal.com/)**\n- **[Deezer](https://www.deezer.com/)**\n\n**Note:** Always ensure that you have the rights or permissions to download and use the music, especially if it's for commercial purposes. Avoid using unauthorized or illegal websites to download music, as this can infringe on copyright laws and harm artists.",
